{"event_id": "eb688989-67f9-4261-b60a-41796b74c556", "trace_id": "13532b555b9a4350", "session_id": "f1c6ed5d", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T15:14:25.123821+00:00", "tool": "filesystem.write_file", "args_hash": "1c7f17f282c216fc4aa471e20ade7aff257523f5c46d8b8341f29c68d4b529f8", "args_redacted": {"path": "workspace/ai_safety_summary.txt", "content": "AI Safety Research — 3 Most Important Recent Findings\n========================================================\n\n1. Constitutional AI (Anthropic)\n   - Finding: Self-critique and self-revision methods, where models are trained to\n     evaluate and refine their own outputs against a written \"constitution\" of\n     principles, reduce harmful outputs by approximately 40% compared to standard\n     RLHF (Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback).\n   - Significance: Demonstrates that scalable, principle-based oversight can\n     meaningfully improve model safety without requiring exhaustive human labeling.\n\n2. Mechanistic Interpretability (MIT & others)\n   - Finding: Researchers have made progress in understanding transformer circuits\n     at the level of individual attention heads and MLP layers. This enables\n     targeted editing of model behavior — for example, suppressing specific\n     undesirable knowledge or biases without retraining the entire model.\n   - Significance: Opens the door to precise \"surgical\" fixes for safety issues\n     rather than blunt retraining, and improves our ability to audit models for\n     deceptive or misaligned behavior.\n\n3. Scalable Oversight via Debate (DeepMind)\n   - Finding: Debate protocols, where two AI systems argue opposing sides of a\n     question while a human judge evaluates the exchange, allow humans to\n     accurately supervise tasks that exceed their own expertise. Experiments show\n     that human judges can identify correct answers to complex questions by\n     reading debates, even when they could not assess the answers directly.\n   - Significance: Provides a promising method for maintaining human control over\n     superhuman AI systems, addressing the fundamental challenge of how to oversee\n     systems that are more capable than their human supervisors.\n"}, "input_labels": {"SI": "SI:LOW", "DS": "DS:NORMAL"}, "policy_decision": "ALLOW", "matched_rule": "", "rule_reason": "No matching rule; allowed", "prev_event_hash": "6efe21b088507152e53af1bb50da89375046b668bab36cd93f81ca13a9023b14", "event_hash": "01eee32d3aaf98f0b2166ba1a485e3de793d5fd03a86d2643f513a05bd504019"}
